cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with improving the accuracy of deep neural networks (DNNs) using Winograd convolution. The primary application of DNNs is in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of different floating-point formats, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NE). The optimization of convolutional operations is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the use of Winograd algorithms involves matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental operation in data science (cs.DS).
